Author:
Vol / Page:
Edition:
Quote:  `Colonel Peerless's Light Infantry' served at the base at Etaples under a medical officer, Colonel Peerless. There were many titles of that kind.
Notes: McNab NZ Slang Press [Slang of the NZEF]

Date: 0/0/1984
Source: Dictionary of Slang
Author: PARTRIDGE
Vol / Page: 240
Edition: 8th
Quote: <i>Colonel Peerless's Light Infantry</i>. NZ soldiers working at the base at Etaples: NZ military: latter half of WW2. Ex Colonel Peerless, the medical officer in charge.
